---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Disclaimer — Aivyx" description="Legal disclaimer for the Aivyx ecosystem.">
  <section class="disclaimer">
    <div class="disclaimer-inner">
      <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: March 7, 2026</p>

      <div class="notice">
        <span class="notice-badge">BETA</span>
        <p>Aivyx is currently in <strong>beta</strong>. The software is under active development and may contain bugs, incomplete features, or breaking changes.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>No Warranty</h2>
      <p>
        Aivyx is provided <strong>"as is"</strong>, without warranty of any kind, express or implied, 
        including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, 
        and non-infringement. In no event shall the authors or copyright holders be liable for any claim, 
        damages, or other liability, whether in an action of contract, tort, or otherwise, arising from, 
        out of, or in connection with the software or the use or other dealings in the software.
      </p>

      <h2>Use at Your Own Risk</h2>
      <p>
        You acknowledge that Aivyx is beta software and you use it entirely at your own risk. The developers 
        make no guarantees regarding:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The reliability, accuracy, or completeness of any output generated by Aivyx or its AI agents</li>
        <li>The availability or uptime of any Aivyx services</li>
        <li>The security of data processed by third-party LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, etc.)</li>
        <li>The preservation of data between software updates or version changes</li>
        <li>Compatibility with any specific hardware, operating system, or software configuration</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>AI-Generated Content</h2>
      <p>
        Aivyx uses large language models (LLMs) to generate responses, analysis, and content. 
        AI-generated content may be inaccurate, incomplete, biased, or misleading. You should 
        independently verify any AI-generated output before relying on it for decisions, 
        especially in professional, legal, medical, financial, or safety-critical contexts.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        When using external LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini), your prompts and data 
        are transmitted to those providers subject to their respective terms of service and privacy 
        policies. Aivyx's local encryption protects data at rest on your machine, but cannot control 
        how third-party providers handle data in transit or at rest on their servers. For maximum privacy, 
        use Ollama for fully local inference.
      </p>

      <h2>Encryption Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        While Aivyx implements industry-standard encryption (ChaCha20Poly1305, HKDF-SHA256), no 
        encryption system is guaranteed to be unbreakable. The security of your data depends on factors 
        including the strength of your passphrase, the security of your operating system, and proper 
        handling of key material. Aivyx has not undergone a formal third-party security audit at this time.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, in no event shall the Aivyx project, its 
        contributors, or affiliates be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential 
        or exemplary damages, including but not limited to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Loss of data, revenue, profits, or business opportunities</li>
        <li>Business interruption or downtime</li>
        <li>Personal injury or property damage</li>
        <li>Any damages arising from reliance on AI-generated content</li>
        <li>Costs of procurement of substitute goods or services</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Open Source License</h2>
      <p>
        Aivyx is distributed under the <a href="https://github.com/AivyxDev/aivyx/blob/main/LICENSE" target="_blank">MIT License</a>. 
        This disclaimer supplements and does not replace the terms of the MIT License.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update this disclaimer at any time. Changes will be reflected on this 
        page with an updated date. Continued use of Aivyx after changes constitutes acceptance of the 
        updated terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this disclaimer, please open an issue on 
        <a href="https://github.com/AivyxDev/aivyx/issues" target="_blank">GitHub</a> or reach out via 
        <a href="https://github.com/AivyxDev/aivyx/discussions" target="_blank">Discussions</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .disclaimer {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
  }
  .disclaimer-inner h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .updated {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .notice {
    background: rgba(232, 168, 73, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .notice-badge {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .notice p {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .notice strong {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .disclaimer-inner h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .disclaimer-inner p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .disclaimer-inner ul {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .disclaimer-inner li {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .disclaimer-inner a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
